{"type":"message","id":"157bc645","parentId":"42a6e764","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:11:29.214Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 12:11 GMT+2] REPO STERILIZATION & CI/CD FINALIZATION.\n\n1.  **Scan for 'OpenClaw' artifacts:**\n    *   Search RECURSIVELY in `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main` (the repo root).\n    *   Look for: `.openclaw`, `openclaw.json`, `logs`, `sessions`, `workspace`, or any file containing the string \"OpenClaw\" (case-insensitive).\n    *   *Constraint:* Be careful NOT to delete the actual bot code if it just mentions \"OpenClaw\" in a comment. Focus on *system files* that shouldn't be in a git repo.\n\n2.  **Backup Strategy:**\n    *   If found (e.g., custom prompts), COPY them to `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\internal`.\n\n3.  **Delete & Git Remove:**\n    *   Delete the files from the repo folder.\n    *   Run `git rm <file>` (or `git add -u` after deletion) to stage the removal.\n    *   *Critical:* Ensure `.gitignore` is updated to exclude `.openclaw/` and `openclaw.json` in the future.\n\n4.  **CI/CD Upgrade:**\n    *   Write the *previously generated* `ci.yml` content to `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.\n    *   Stage: `git add .github/workflows/ci.yml`.\n\n5.  **Commit & Push:**\n    *   Commit: `chore: Sterilize repo (remove internal configs) and upgrade CI to Python 3.14`.\n    *   Push to `origin/dev`.\n\n6.  **Final Audit:**\n    *   Run a quick check: `git ls-files` | grep \"openclaw\" (should be empty).\n\n7.  **Report:**\n    *   List of deleted files.\n    *   List of backed up files.\n    *   CI/CD update status.\n    *   Confirmation of clean repo."}],"timestamp":1771150289212}}
