{"type":"message","id":"ac569073","parentId":"064a851e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:11:55.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Investigating Fallbacks**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `dmarket_api.py` file, and I've found it utilizes `openclaw.json` as a fallback configuration. This suggests a potential dependency and a specific location search strategy. I'm noting the implications of this approach.\n\n\n**Evaluating Configuration Dependencies**\n\nMy recent investigation of `dmarket_api.py` revealed its direct reliance on `openclaw.json` for fallback configuration. The code searches a specific path. I've decided to leave the configuration loading logic intact to avoid removing bot code; instead, I will focus on removing the files the code *expects* to exist to truly sterilize it. This includes `openclaw.json` and any logs. I'm noting potential future issues related to this design.\n\n\n**Prioritizing File System Changes**\n\nThe `dmarket_api.py` analysis confirms my suspicions. I'm choosing a non-destructive path to \"sterilization,\" focusing on removing associated files such as `openclaw.json` and preventing future generation of undesirable artifacts. I'm now composing a `.gitignore` file, and plan to move over the `ci.yml` file, completing this first major change.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771150315723_263","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\temp_dmarket_bot\\.github\\workflows\\ci.yml"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":7449,"output":683,"cacheRead":5127,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8132,"cost":{"input":0.014898,"output":0.008196,"cacheRead":0.0010254,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0241194}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771150306016}}
{"type":"message","id":"91d140c7","parentId":"ac569073","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:11:55.743Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771150315723_263","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: CI\r\n\r\non:\r\n  push:\r\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\r\n    paths-ignore:\r\n      - '**.md'\r\n      - 'docs/**'\r\n  pull_request:\r\n    branches: [ \"main\" ]\r\n    paths-ignore:\r\n      - '**.md'\r\n      - 'docs/**'\r\n\r\npermissions:\r\n  contents: read\r\n\r\njobs:\r\n  build:\r\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\r\n    strategy:\r\n      matrix:\r\n        python-version: [\"3.11\"]\r\n\r\n    steps:\r\n    - uses: actions/checkout@v4\r\n    \r\n    - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\r\n      uses: actions/setup-python@v5\r\n      with:\r\n        python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\r\n        cache: 'pip'\r\n        \r\n    - name: Install dependencies\r\n      run: |\r\n        python -m pip install --upgrade pip\r\n        if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\r\n        pip install ruff pytest pytest-asyncio\r\n        \r\n    - name: Lint with Ruff\r\n      run: |\r\n        # Stop the build if there are Python syntax errors or undefined names\r\n        ruff check src/ --select E9,F63,F7,F82 --output-format=github\r\n        # Default run (exit non-zero on error)\r\n        ruff check src/ --exit-non-zero-on-fix\r\n        \r\n    - name: Test with pytest\r\n      run: |\r\n        # Run unit tests only to keep CI fast\r\n        # Ignoring integration tests that require external services\r\n        pytest tests/unit/ --ignore=tests/integration --ignore=tests/e2e\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771150315741}}
