{"type":"message","id":"8cd047a5","parentId":"fc2c8ae4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T10:12:10.132Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Crafting CI Configuration**\n\nI've established the directory structure and am now diligently writing the configuration files. Specifically, I am updating the `ci.yml` file, systematically replacing the Python version reference. Furthermore, I'm constructing a `.gitignore` file, and I've included the necessary exclusions, especially the all-important `.env` file to ensure security. I will then continue with the planned execution.\n\n\n**Constructing the Workflow**\n\nThe `ci.yml` file is being meticulously refined, specifically replacing the initial Python version indicator. Simultaneously, I've populated the `.gitignore` with the required exclusions, with `.env` included. I'm preparing to execute the git commands, ensuring the code base is prepared.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771150330131_265","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main\\.github\\workflows\\ci.yml","content":"name: CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n    paths-ignore:\n      - '**.md'\n      - 'docs/**'\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n    paths-ignore:\n      - '**.md'\n      - 'docs/**'\n\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.14\"]\n\n    steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n    \n    - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      uses: actions/setup-python@v5\n      with:\n        python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        cache: 'pip'\n        \n    - name: Install dependencies\n      run: |\n        python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n        if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n        pip install ruff pytest pytest-asyncio\n        \n    - name: Lint with Ruff\n      run: |\n        # Stop the build if there are Python syntax errors or undefined names\n        ruff check src/ --select E9,F63,F7,F82 --output-format=github\n        # Default run (exit non-zero on error)\n        ruff check src/ --exit-non-zero-on-fix\n        \n    - name: Test with pytest\n      run: |\n        # Run unit tests only to keep CI fast\n        # Ignoring integration tests that require external services\n        # If tests/unit/ doesn't exist, we skip to prevent failure on empty repo\n        if [ -d \"tests/unit\" ]; then\n          pytest tests/unit/ --ignore=tests/integration --ignore=tests/e2e\n        else\n          echo \"No unit tests found, skipping...\"\n        fi\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":8480,"output":586,"cacheRead":7783,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9066,"cost":{"input":0.01696,"output":0.007032,"cacheRead":0.0015566000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0255486}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771150321957}}
